@KeycloakLab4_HostAddress = http://localhost:5277
@token_endpoint = http://localhost:8081/realms/myrealm/protocol/openid-connect/token
@client_id = lab4-client
@username = your-user
@password = your-password

### 1. Get tokens (password grant → returns access_token AND refresh_token)
POST {{token_endpoint}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id={{client_id}}&username={{username}}&password={{password}}&scope=openid

### 2. Public endpoint (no token)
GET {{KeycloakLab4_HostAddress}}/public
Accept: application/json

### 3. Protected — paste access_token below; works until it expires
GET {{KeycloakLab4_HostAddress}}/protected
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### 4. Token-info — watch remainingSeconds shrink on repeat calls
GET {{KeycloakLab4_HostAddress}}/token-info
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### 5. Refresh — after access token expires, mint a new one (no re-login)
POST {{token_endpoint}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=refresh_token&client_id={{client_id}}&refresh_token={{refresh_token}}
